{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"63edd385-b3f4-4b58-ac95-3559baf7883a","content":"Good news — on .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft Testing Platform **by default**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a .NET 9 opt-in bridge and is no longer needed.\n\nYou can simply remove it:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01TXBKEeCiT6HMY7qBfLYJSE","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01467P4VWta76jKJryq2xKt5","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-d2beb9f5a3ad4ed88cd75f036655fdd5/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-d2beb9f5a3ad4ed88cd75f036655fdd5/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"263aab36-2cb0-420f-a6df-177b41120aed","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about MTP support. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. This was a bridge property introduced in .NET 9 to opt into MTP support, but in .NET 10, MTP is the default test runner for `dotnet test`.\n\nSo they can remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` from their project file. The `EnableMSTestRunner` property is still needed to enable the MSTest runner (which makes the test project an executable that uses MTP).\n\n\nI'll show them what their updated project file should look like.","outputTokens":467,"requestId":"042E:1CF5FA:1DF7A5E:21CE356:69E81AC2"},"id":"9033905b-2af5-4ecf-9fdc-fb144e16d530","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:48:10.826Z","parentId":"48477d5e-09e3-4596-8ef8-133024a76e23"}
