{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4812ed31-799f-4004-8924-73d2f77c67d8","content":"Here's the summary:\n\n- **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` → remove it.** In .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively routes to MTP. That property was a .NET 9 opt-in and is now a no-op.\n- **`EnableMSTestRunner` → keep it.** This tells MSTest to build your test project as an MTP executable, which is still required.\n- **`OutputType Exe` → keep it.** Needed for the MTP runner entry point.\n\nYour `dotnet test` will now use MTP directly without the VSTest compatibility layer. No other changes needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"263aab36-2cb0-420f-a6df-177b41120aed","outputTokens":151,"requestId":"042E:1CF5FA:1DF9B23:21D0A38:69E81ACD"},"id":"016eca6d-5c96-4a2e-9ee9-bb47b4e982ba","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:48:18.667Z","parentId":"ac47375b-19ce-4788-8124-11020dd56827"}
